CS 214 Spring 2026 - Project III: mysh
=======================================
Name: Numair Hasan, Darren Chuang
NetID: MNH83, dlc286


Overview
--------
mysh is a simple Unix shell that supports interactive and batch modes,
built-in commands, I/O redirection, pipelines, and glob expansion.


Building
--------
    make

This produces the executable ./mysh.

Usage
-----
    ./mysh              # interactive mode if stdin is a terminal
    ./mysh script.sh    # batch mode from a file
    cat script.sh | ./mysh  # batch mode from a pipe


Features Implemented
--------------------
- readline() using read() one byte at a time, no buffered I/O
- Tokenizer that handles whitespace, #comments, and |, <, > as solo tokens
- Interactive mode: prompt showing current directory with ~ for HOME,
  welcome/goodbye messages, exit status reporting after each command
- Batch mode: no prompt or messages, child stdin defaults to /dev/null
- Built-in commands: cd, pwd, which, exit
- Program search in /usr/local/bin, /usr/bin, /bin (in that order)
- Direct path execution when name contains /
- I/O redirection with < and >
- Pipelines with | connecting multiple sub-commands
- Glob/wildcard expansion for tokens containing *
  - Patterns starting with * do not match hidden (dot) files
  - Unmatched patterns passed through unchanged
- exit works inside pipelines (e.g. foo | exit)


Test Plan
---------

1. readline / tokenize
   - Empty line -> no tokens, shell continues
   - Line with only a comment: "# hello" -> no tokens
   - Mixed: "echo hi # comment" -> 2 tokens: echo, hi
   - Special chars as tokens: "echo foo > bar" -> 4 tokens

2. Built-ins
   - pwd: prints working directory
   - cd with no args: goes to $HOME
   - cd subdir: changes into subdir, prompt updates
   - cd too_many args: prints error
   - cd nonexistent: prints error from chdir
   - which ls: prints /bin/ls
   - which cd: prints nothing (cd is a builtin)
   - which fakecmd: prints nothing
   - exit: prints goodbye and quits

3. External programs
   - echo hello world: runs /bin/echo, prints output
   - /bin/ls: direct path works
   - fakecmd: prints "not found" error

4. Redirection
   - echo hello > out.txt: creates file with "hello"
   - cat < out.txt: reads from file
   - echo hi > out.txt < /dev/null: both redirects on one command

5. Pipelines
   - echo hello | cat: output flows through pipe
   - ls | grep mysh | cat: multi-stage pipeline
   - last command's exit status reported

6. Wildcards
   - ls *.c: expands to all .c files
   - ls *.txt with no matches: passes *.txt literally
   - *.c does not match .hidden.c

7. Interactive vs batch
   - ./mysh < script.sh: no prompt printed
   - ./mysh script.sh: same
   - ./mysh in terminal: prompt shown, status shown after errors

8. Exit status reporting
   - false (exits 1): prints "Exited with status 1"
   - kill -TERM $$: prints "Terminated by signal ..."

Test inputs used
----------------
